===Etymology===
From {{etyl|peo}} {{term|𐎠𐎼𐎷𐎡𐎴|sc=Xpeo|lang=peo|tr=Armina}} (late 6th century BC), {{etyl|grc}} {{term|Ἀρμενία|sc=polytonic|tr=Armenia|lang=grc}} (early 5th century BC). The further etymology of the Persian name is uncertain, but may be connected to the {{etyl|akk}} {{rfscript|Cuneiform}} ''Armânum, Armanî'' and/or the Biblical ''Minni''. See [[w:Name of Armenia|Name of Armenia]] article for theories. The Old Persian name is an [[exonym]]: see {{term|հայ||sc=Armn|tr=hay|lang=hy}} for the native name and [[w:Urartu|Urartu]] for the Biblical ''[[Ararat]]''.

